The '''Central Election Commission of Abkhazia''' is the body responsible for conducting national [[elections in Abkhazia|elections]] and overseeing local elections in [[Abkhazia]]. It was first formed on 20 July 1991.<ref name=rrc294>{{cite news|title=DECREE ISSUED BY THE PRESIDIUM OF THE SUPREME COUNCIL OF THE ABKHAZ ASSR on Establishment of the Central Electoral Commission on election of the Deputies to the Supreme Council of the Abkhaz ASSR|url=http://www.rrc.ge/law/dadg_1991_07_20_e.htm?lawid=294&lng_3=en|accessdate=21 July 2012|date=20 July 1991}}</ref>
==Chairmen== The first chairman of the Central Election Commission was [[Viacheslav Tsugba]],<ref name=rrc294/> who held the post until he became Prime Minister in 1999.
On 11 October 2004, [[Sergei Smyr]] resigned during the height of the crisis following the [[Abkhazian presidential election, 2004|Presidential election]] earlier that month.<ref name=uzel64962>{{cite news|title=Абхазия: выборы президента|url=http://www.kavkaz-uzel.ru/articles/64962/|accessdate=21 July 2012|newspaper=[[Caucasian Knot]]|date=February 2005}}</ref> On 14 December, the newly formed Central Election Commission elected former Justice Minister [[Batal Tabagua]] as its chairman.<ref name=uzel66397>{{cite news|last=Kuchuberia|first=Anzhela|title=Председателем ЦИК Абхазии избран экс-министр юстиции Батал Табагуа|url=http://www.kavkaz-uzel.ru/articles/66397/|accessdate=21 July 2012|newspaper=[[Caucasian Knot]]|date=12 December 2004}}</ref>
In 2016, Tabagua was not re-appointed to the Central Election Commission, and on 23 December, former State Privatisation Committee Chairman [[Tamaz Gogia]] was elected his successor during the first meeting of the CEC in its new composition.<ref name="inform5093">{{cite news|title=ТАМАЗ ГОГИЯ ИЗБРАН ПРЕДСЕДАТЕЛЕМ ЦЕНТРАЛЬНОЙ ИЗБИРАТЕЛЬНОЙ КОМИССИИ|url=http://abkhazinform.com/item/5093-tamaz-gogiya-izbran-predsedatelem-tsentralnoj-izbiratelnoj-komissii|accessdate=27 February 2017|agency=[[Abkhazia Inform]]|date=23 December 2016}}</ref>
